                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="12981997" author="jvs" created="Sat, 15 Jan 2011 01:24:55 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I tried debugging this one yesterday and noticed that if I kill the scribed daemon, then the test works.  Is it possible that a zookeeper-enabled scribe running on the machines in question is causing port conflicts?  Try running on a freshly restarted machine to confirm.&lt;/p&gt;
</comment>
                            <comment id="12989831" author="jvs" created="Wed, 2 Feb 2011 22:20:14 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I confirmed that this is due to a conflict with ports opened by existing services; I&apos;m adding a patch which makes the test ports dynamic.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12989953" author="jvs" created="Thu, 3 Feb 2011 03:36:53 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://reviews.apache.org/r/385/&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://reviews.apache.org/r/385/&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Note that I did not make the zookeeper ports dynamic since we have not seen an issue there yet, but we may need to do that as a followup if we hit it.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12989976" author="namit" created="Thu, 3 Feb 2011 05:53:38 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;looks good to me&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12990197" author="namit" created="Thu, 3 Feb 2011 17:47:32 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Committed. Thanks John&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
